# HTTP Basics

## 1. What problem does it solve?
HTTP allows clients (browser/apps) to communicate with servers.

## 2. Key Concepts
- Request
- Response
- Headers
- Status codes
- Methods (GET POST PUT DELETE)

## 3. Example
GET /users
Host: api.example.com

Response:
200 OK
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Anshika"
}

## 4. Where it appears in my project
Used when creating API endpoints in FastAPI.

Example:
GET /events
POST /events

## 5. Things that confused me
Difference between PUT vs PATCH



# HTTP Methods

## Problem
Client needs different ways to interact with server resources.

## Methods
GET → retrieve data
POST → create data
PUT → replace data
PATCH → update data
DELETE → remove data

## Example

GET /events

POST /events
{
 "name": "Hackathon"
}

## In My Project
Used in Event Ledger API

GET /events
POST /events
DELETE /events/{id}

## Mistakes I Made
Sent GET request instead of POST

## Interview Questions
Difference between PUT and PATCH

