#DAY 1 

1. Flask Application Factory Pattern
Interview Definition

The Application Factory Pattern in Flask is a design pattern where the Flask app is created inside a function rather than as a global variable.

This allows:

modular architecture

easier testing

multiple app instances with different configurations.


basic syntax 

from flask import Flask

def create_app():
    app = Flask(__name__)
    return app

Q)) why not just from flask import flask and then app = flask(__name__)
	-creates problems in larger systems 
circular imports = modules depend on each other 
harder testing= cannot create multiple app instances
config issues = env based configs harder

IMPLEMENTATION 
from flask import Flask //Imports flask class used to create web server 

def create_app(): //factory fn that builds and returns flask app 
     app = Flask(__name__) //initialise and create flask application object and --name-- helps flask locate templates,static files and modules 
    @app.route("/") //define route-registers a url endpoint 
    def home(): //route handler and calls a python dict 
        return {"message": "EventLedger API running"}

    @app.route("/health")
    def health():
        return {"status": "healthy"}

    return app

SERVER ENTRY POINT(run.py)
starts flask server - seperates application logic and startup 

from app import create_app

app = create_app()

if __name__ == "__main__":  //files runs only when executed directly and not when imported
    app.run(debug=True) //starts flask development server

REQUEST FLOW

Client
 ↓
Flask Server
 ↓
Route Matching
 ↓
health() function
 ↓
Return JSON
 ↓
HTTP Response


Time complexity - route lookup in flask uses a has-based routing table 
avg lookup complexity -	O(1)

health endpoint is used by monitoring systems to verify whether the backend service is running 

create_app() is responsible for initializing the entire application env including databse connections,extensions, routes and configs
run.py starts the sever 
routes onyl handle https request,responses,business logic calls 
